comment_data.body:
I may be wrong but couldn't you just check that `config->win != curwin->handle` instead of fetching and comparing the pointers? That way this could still be a single statement like below and no checks for the actual window need to be done in `parse_float_config`, since validation is done in `nvim_open_win` and `nvim_win_set_config`.

```lua
if (!reconf || config->win != curwin->handle) {
  fconfig->window = curwin->handle;
}
```

